The paper deals with the analysis of a popular reinforcement learning algorithm, TD(0), with function approximation. This falls under the broad category of machine learning, specifically reinforcement learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the convergence properties of the algorithm, which is related to control theory and optimization, covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper uses concentration bounds and information theory techniques, which are covered by cs.IT (Information Theory).
